<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This function takes an error, and appends a string of text to the end of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that error. Since &quot;appending&quot; to an Error isn&#39;t supported behavior of an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Error, this function technically creates a new error with the combined</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><Highlight kind="comment">/// message and consumes the old error.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
